Interface SparseVector<T extends Number>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Vector<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SparseDoubleVector, SparseIntegerVector
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AmortizedSparseVector, AtomicSparseVector, CompactSparseIntegerVector, CompactSparseVector, MaskedSparseDoubleVectorView, ScaledSparseDoubleVector, SparseHashDoubleVector, SparseHashIntegerVector, SparseHashVector, TernaryVector

    public interface SparseVector<T extends Number>
extends Vector<T>
    An interface for Vector implementations whose values are sparse and that support access to only those indices with non-zero values.

    Keith Stevens
